  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "When you open a Swift package (a directory containing a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Package.swift",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " file), the extension automatically generates build tasks and launch configurations for each executable within the package. Additionally, if the package includes tests, the extension creates a configuration specifically designed to run those tests. These configurations all leverage the CodeLLDB extension as the debugger of choice.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "Debugging workflows are common to all VS Code extensions. See the ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier" : "https:\/\/code.visualstudio.com\/docs\/debugtest\/testing",
                  "isActive" : true,
                  "type" : "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " for a more in-depth overview.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "Debugging works best when using a version of the Swift toolchain 6.0 or higher.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "💡 Tip",
          "style" : "note",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Use the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "Run > Start Debugging",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "strong"
            },
            {
              "text" : " menu item to run an executable and start debugging. If you have multiple launch configurations you can choose which launch configuration to use in the debugger view.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Launch-Configurations",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Launch Configurations",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The Swift extension will automatically generate launch configurations for all of your executable products. You can customize these configurations via the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : ".vscode\/launch.json",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " file in your workspace to add environment variables, arguments, etc.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Each generated launch configuration will have the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "\"type\"",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " set to ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "\"swift\"",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ". The properties for the swift launch configuration match the ones ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/marketplace.visualstudio.com\/items?itemName=llvm-vs-code-extensions.lldb-dap",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : ". You can use code completion in VS Code to help with adding properties to your launch configuration.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Launching-an-Executable",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Launching an Executable",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The most basic launch configuration uses the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "\"launch\"",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " request and provides a program that will be debugged. For example:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "{",
            "    \"label\": \"Debug my-executable\", \/\/ Human readable name for the configuration",
            "    \"type\": \"swift\",                \/\/ All Swift launch configurations use the same type",
            "    \"request\": \"launch\",            \/\/ Launch an executable",
            "    \"program\": \"${workspaceFolder}\/.build\/debug\/my-executable\"",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "javascript",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "program",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " property supports a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "${binPath}",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " variable that resolves to the relative path from the build directory to the binary output directory. This is useful because the binary output location can vary depending on the Swift build system in use (e.g. ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : ".build\/debug",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " vs ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : ".build\/out\/Products\/Debug",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : "):",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "{",
            "    \"label\": \"Debug my-executable\",",
            "    \"type\": \"swift\",",
            "    \"request\": \"launch\",",
            "    \"program\": \"${workspaceFolder}\/.build\/${binPath}\/my-executable\",",
            "    \"configuration\": \"debug\"",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "javascript",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "For SwiftPM based projects, you may specify a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "target",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "configuration",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " instead of a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "program",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " to make your debug configurations shareable between different developers on different platforms:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "{",
            "    \"label\": \"Debug my-executable\", \/\/ Human readable name for the configuration",
            "    \"type\": \"swift\",                \/\/ All Swift launch configurations use the same type",
            "    \"request\": \"launch\",            \/\/ Launch an executable",
            "    \"target\": \"my-executable\",",
            "    \"configuration\": \"debug\"",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "javascript",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "There are many more options that you can specify which will alter the behavior of the debugger:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
